in: As appears in colophon (fol.21a), copied (and possibly also composed) by royal scribe (kātib al-sulṭānī) Muḥammad Ḥusayn al-Ṭihrānī with transcription completed Muḥarram 1268 [October-November 1851].</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Former shelfmark: "391 T. De M. [i.e. Tammaro De Marinis]" inscribed in pencil on recto of front flyleaf.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Binding: Boards covered in orange-red leather with gray-brown leather over spine and edges / turn-ins (turned-out doublures, framed binding, compare Isl. Ms. 302) ; Type III binding (without flap) ; doublures in same gray-brown leather ; upper and lower covers carry border and central ornament faintly stained in the leather ; sewn in spring green thread, six stations ; overall in fairly good condition with some staining, minor abrasion etc.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Support: European wove paper ; highly burnished.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Decoration: Some keywords rubricated, many others in blue, turquoise, etc. ; some vocalization rubricated ; textual dividers in the form of red discs ; written area surrounded by heavy frame in gold with red and blue fillets, margins bordered in much narrower bands of red and gold ; text of incipit and facing page set of by gold (now gone to dark green) cloud-bands ; in some places written area flecked with gold (now green).</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Script: Nastaʻlīq ; large, elegant hand ; serifless, with slight effect of words descending to baseline, closed counters, elongation and exaggerated thickness of horizontal strokes ; partially vocalized.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Layout: Written in 7 lines per page ; frame-ruled.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Collation: i, IV (8), III (14), III+1 (21), i ; quaternion and two ternions.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Dedication: Dedicated to Nāṣir al-Dīn Shāh Qājār (see fol.20a).</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Colophon: "Scribal," reads "كاتب السلطانى محمد حسين الطهرانى مسوده نموده فى شهر محرم الحرام سنه ١٢۶۸"</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Incipit: "الحمد لله رب العالمین والصلوة والسلام على خیر خلقه محمد وآله اجمعین اما بعد حکیمی سپر انرا پند همیداد ..."</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Title supplied by cataloguer.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Ms. codex.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="520" ind1="8" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Fine copy of a work of advice literature of uncertain authorship.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="538" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Mode of access: Internet.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="541" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="c">Purchase ;</subfield><subfield code="a">Acquired by purchase (funds donated by Horace Rackham).</subfield><subfield code="d">1924.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Persian.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="561" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Inscription in pencil on front flyleaf "391 T. De M. [i.e. Tammaro De Marinis]" ; also on front flyleaf, inscription identifying copyist "نصايح نامه خط ميرزا حسين طهرانى" ; fairly clean copy.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="650" ind1=" " ind2="0"><subfield code="a">Manuscripts, Persian</subfield><subfield code="z">Michigan</subfield><subfield code="z">Ann Arbor.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="650" ind1=" " ind2="0"><subfield code="a">Didactic literature, Persian.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="